A good default that I use is that soprano voices are nicer girls and usually shorter, whereas altos are taller and meaner.
But I just as often break the mold. In my current, the alto is the nice girl and older lower due to size.
As for timbre, this is something best showed by how the character speaks. You don't need to pile adjective upon adjective. Just have her dialogue pace faster on average and the reader will get it. Then you can vary that pace up or down to show how ebullient she is at the moment.

tl;dr reading your character's dialogue out loud is a good practice
